General
All div elements have an xml:id with the uri stated in an idno element
All div elements have a @resp attribute. It would be great to see the name on the factoid page
In person factoids, the persName directly nested under person indicates the subject even if other person URIs appear elsewhere
Person factoids can be about individuals person or groups personGrp
Any factoid may contain a URN in bibl but not all do. We should pull the primary text in when we can.

Name variants (person and personGrp)
            <div type="factoid" xml:id="factoid-40" resp="#ktorabi">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/10510-40</idno>
                <listPerson>
                    <personGrp>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3669"> The monks who resided in
                                <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/399"> the Convent of John
                                Urtaya in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/8"
                                    >Amida</placeName></placeName></persName>
                    </personGrp>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/10510"/><citedRange
                        unit="pp">555</citedRange></bibl>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2033"/><citedRange
                        unit="pp">209</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>


