Event factoid: 
note the listRelation for linking this factoid to another
note that any factoid may contain a URN in the bibl 
            <div type="factoid" xml:id="factoid-545" resp="#dschwartz">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/8559-545</idno>
                <listEvent>
                    <event ana="http://syriaca.org/keyword/natural-disasters">
                        <desc> The first time the walls of <placeName
                                ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78"> Edessa </placeName> were broken
                            down was in <choice>
                                <reg><date when="0201-11" calendar="Gregorian"
                                        srophe:computed-start="0201-11-01">November A. D.
                                        201</date></reg>
                                <orig><date when-custom="0513-02"
                                        datingMethod="Seleucid-SyriacMonths">Teshri II A. Gr.
                                        513</date></orig>
                            </choice></desc>
                    </event>
                    <listRelation>
                        <relation ref="syriaca:SameEvent" ana="event"
                            mutual="http://syriaca.org/spear/8559-18 http://syriaca.org/spear/8559-545"
                        />
                    </listRelation>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/633"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">13</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="urn">
                    <ptr target="urn:cts:syriacLit:nhsl8559.syriacCorpus57:106"/>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/657"/>
                    <citedRange unit="part">106</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>

Relation factoid: mutual
We've avoided using a note element for a prose description of the relation element. Let me know if that is still workable.
            <div type="factoid" xml:id="factoid-3" resp="#mdoerfler #jnsaint-laurent">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/814-3</idno>
                <listRelation>
                    <relation ref="snap:SiblingOf"
                        type="snap:MaternalFamilyRelationship snap:HalfFamilyRelationship"
                        mutual="http://syriaca.org/person/1117 http://syriaca.org/person/1548"/>
                </listRelation>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/814"/><citedRange
                        unit="pp">299</citedRange></bibl>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/814"/><citedRange
                        unit="pp">299</citedRange></bibl>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1409"/><citedRange
                        unit="pp">299</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>
			

Relation factoid: reciprocal
            <div type="factoid" xml:id="factoid-52" resp="#ktorabi">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/10510-52</idno>
                <listRelation>
                    <relation ref="syriaca:MonasticHeadOver" active="http://syriaca.org/person/3227"
                        passive="http://syriaca.org/person/3669"/>
                </listRelation>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/10510"/><citedRange
                        unit="pp">556</citedRange></bibl>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2033"/><citedRange
                        unit="pp">210</citedRange></bibl>
            </div>



Discursive notes
These can nest directly under the div element 
They are similar to a footnote. We might need to think a bit about how to display this information.
            <div type="factoid" xml:id="factoid-25" resp="#ktorabi #dschwartz">
                <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/spear/3038-25</idno>
                <listPerson>
                    <personGrp>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3051"> Those attending the synod at
                            Commanus in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/576"> Armenia
                            </placeName> in <date when="0458"> 458 </date></persName>
                    </personGrp>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary"><ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/668"/><citedRange
                        unit="part">1.13</citedRange><citedRange unit="pp">55</citedRange></bibl>
                <note> This date comes from Honigman. <bibl type="secondary"><ptr
                            target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/1379"/><citedRange unit="pp"
                            >119</citedRange></bibl></note>
            </div>


